ZCZC OE02
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 062300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER
THE S OF FITZROY 986 WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE
EXTENDING E FM ICELAND ACROSS SCANDINAVIA AND INTO THE
BALTIC. THE LOW WILL MOV NW AND FILL DURING MONDAY WITH A
NEW LOW 999 DEVELOPING IN THE S OF BISCAY BY MIDNIGHT
TUESDAY. DURING TUESDAY THIS LOW IS ALSO EXP TO MOV NW
INTO SOLE AND SLWY FILL AS ANOTHER LOW 996 DEVELOPS OVER
THE S OF BISCAY DURING WEDNESDAY. THE RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE FM ICELAND EWARDS TO THE BALTIC IS EXP TO
PERSIST THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD. OCCASIONAL STRG MAINLY E
TO NE WINDS ARE EXP IN MOST AREAS THROUGHOUT MUCH OF THE
PERIOD BUT WINDS WILL BE GENERALLY LIGHT IN FAIR ISLE AT
FIRST AND REMAIN GENERALLY LIGHT IN S-E ICELAND THROUGH
